How to transfer your DVDs to your Android Tablet Suppose your kids want to watch their DVDs in the car on their Android tablet&hellip;
Here is what you can do (on a Mac OSX 10.9.5):
 install Handbrake and its CLI   $ brew cask install handbrake $ brew cask install handbrakecli   install libdvdcss (thanks to lifehacker&rsquo;s article) in order to bypass copy protection   $ brew install libdvdcss   go to the place where you will place the ripped DVD:   $ cd ~/Movies   convert your DVDs:   $ HandBrakeCLI -i /Volumes/'my DVD' -o /Volumes/Untitled/Movies/my_dvd.
